news.title: Rajasthan: RHB to launch new housing schemes in five districts
news.para: As part of the schemes, the board will offer both flats and independent houses for various income groups, including EWS, LIG, MIG, and HIG.

news.title: Kolkata records 9% growth in office rentals in Q1 2025
news.para: Despite this decrease, the city's average transacted office rents rose by 9%, reaching Rs 42/sq ft/month — the highest among the top eight cities, alongside Hyderabad.

news.title: Jharkhand government announces new townships across eight cities to address urban housing needs
news.para: The department of urban development and housing has begun the groundwork for this ambitious project under which around 400 to 500 acres of land will be acquired in each location.

news.title: RBI cuts repo rate by 25 basis points
news.para: As expected, the Monetary Policy Committee (MPC), which consists of three RBI and three external members, cut the repo rate by 25 basis points to 6.00%.

news.title: Delhi: DDA extends deadline for two housing schemes till April 30
news.para: DDA stated on Tuesday that bookings under both schemes would now reopen from April 9 and continue till April 30 midnight. "The remaining unsold flats will be available for booking,"

news.title: Maharashtra government to promote artificial sand usage
news.para: The use of m-sand or manufactured sand will be subsequently made compulsory, a statement from the Chief Minister's Office stated.

news.title: hBits gets SEBI's nod to launch its SM REIT
news.para: The company plans to launch its maiden SM REIT IPO by June. Over the next few weeks, hBits will also migrate its existing portfolio of commercial properties into the SM REIT structure.

news.title: Delhi government plans to renovate distribute 52,000 flats to slum-dwellers
news.para: ​​​A fund of Rs 700 crore in the Delhi Urban Shelter Improvement Board (DUSIB) has been allocated to Delhi Urban Shelter Improvement Board (DUSIB) for the welfare of those residing in slums,"

news.title: Maharashtra cabinet approves joint redevelopment of two MHADA layouts in Mumbai
news.para: The cabinet approved a floor space index (FSI) of four for the redevelopment. Mhada will get housing stock equivalent to one FSI in both layouts.

news.title: Kolkata civic body mandates information boards for all under-construction buildings
news.para: The building department engineers in the borough were asked to take note of buildings where promoters are not following the rule and issue a stop-work notice.

news.title: Delhi government to develop portal to prevent property fraud
news.para: Officials said the portal would make the registration of the sale deed of properties convenient and corruption-free. It will include a list of those properties booked by civic agencies for illegal construction.

news.title: Maharashtra minister reviews implementation of MHADB projects
news.para: Pankaj Bhoya, minister of state for housing, Maharashtra directed that all stages of implementation be executed within stipulated timelines and that necessary administrative action be initiated to ensure the timely delivery of housing units as per eligibility norms.

news.title: CREDAI-MCHI and PEATA urge Maharashtra deputy CM to restore online access to Mumbai's property databases
news.para: These digital resources were widely used by architects, engineers, developers, and individual property owners to verify details, plan construction, and secure timely approvals.

news.title: Signatureglobal (India) reports pre-sales of ₹102.9 billion in FY25
news.para: Signatureglobal (India) launched five new projects having a combined gross development value (GDV) of approximately ₹138.1 billion. Average sales realization improved to ₹12,457 per sq ft in FY25 from ₹11,762 in FY24.

news.title: Airport Authority officials to inspect land for second airport in Bengaluru
news.para: The Karnataka State Industrial and Infrastructure Development Corporation (KSIIDC) managing director Khushboo Goel Chowdhary briefed the AAI team about the proposed three places identified by the govt for setting up the airport.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC set to launch e-marketplace for TDR this week
news.para: The BMC has created the TDR marketplace on a SAAS platform. All Development Rights Certificates (DRC) will be dematerialised and maintained in an electronic format.

news.title: Lukewarm response to KHB’s project in Mysuru
news.para: As per the proposal, the board wanted to build 160 2 BHK apartments and 32 three BHK apartments. Rs 49.4 lakh was fixed as the provisional rate for two BHK apartments, while Rs 63 lakh was fixed for three BHK apartments.

news.title: SC upholds Bombay HC permit for high-rise building in Chembur
news.para: Aggrieved by the High Court order, AAI went to the Supreme Court to appeal. The Supreme Court on April 7 dismissed AAI’s special leave petition.

news.title: Leasing of retail spaces rise 55% across top eight cities to over 24 lakh sq ft in Q4 FY25: Report
news.para: "India's retail sector is evolving at a dynamic pace, and the strong leasing activity in Q1 2025 reflects growing market confidence," Saurabh Shatdal, Managing Director, Capital Markets and Head-Retail, India said.

news.title: Cement prices expected to rise in April 2025 as government spending increases
news.para: The financial services company further added in the report that, following a dip in prices in March after three months of improvement, the outlook for the coming months appears more optimistic.
